Definition: causing fear or dread or terror
Example: the awful war; an awful risk; dire news; a career or vengeance so direful that London was shocked; the dread presence of the headmaster; polio is no longer the dreaded disease it once was; a dreadful storm; a fearful howling; horrendous explosions shook the city; a terrible curse
Synonyms: noun, attribute, awfulness, dire, direful, dread, a, feeling, dreaded, dreadful, fearful, fearsome, frightening, horrendous, horrific, terrible, terribleness, causing, fear, or, terror, the, war, an, risk, news, career, vengeance, so, that, London, was, shocked, presence, of, headmaster, polio, is, no, longer, disease, it, once, storm, howling, explosions, shook, city, curse
Category: adj.all
